tifiable Jewish minority in Georgia, South and North Carolina from 1860 to 1880. Reconstruction, it is concluded, has to be seen as a formative period for the region’s Jewish congregations and Reform Judaism. The study challenges existing views that are claiming German Jews were setting the standard for Jewish life in this period and were perceived as distinct from Jews of another background. Rather Hieke arrives at a conclusion that takes into consideration the migratory movement between North and South.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aJewszSouthern StatesxHistory. 0aJewszSouthern StatesxIdentity. 0aJudaismzSouthern StatesxHistory. 0aReconstruction (U.S. history, 1865-1877). 4aCarolina. 4aGeorgia. 4aIdentität. 4aIntegration. 4aUSA. 4ajüdische Immigration. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aCarolina.  aGeorgia.  aIdentity.  aIntegration.  aJewish Immigration.  aUSA.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE HISTORY, POLITICAL SCIENCE, SOCIOLOGY  2013z978311031712108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET GESCHICHTE, POLITIKWISS., SOZIOLOGIE  2013z9783110317114oZDB-23-DPS0 cprintz978311027769240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311027774640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110277746423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110277746/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-031712-1  E-BOOK